Request: (assuming AI model A sends a request to AI model B)

```json
{
  "request": {
    "type": "translate",
    "input": "Hello, how are you today?",
    "sourceLanguage": "en",
    "targetLanguage": "fr"
  }
}
```

Response: ( AI model B generates a translation and sends a response)

```json
{
  "response": {
    "translation": "Bonjour, comment √ßa vous va aujourd'hui?"
  }
}
```

In this example, AI model A asks AI model B to translate a sentence from English to French. AI model B accepts the request, processes it, and sends back the translated text in the response. This way, both models can understand each other and communicate efficiently. The JSON format's simplicity and versatility make it an ideal choice for structured AI-to-AI communication.

